models package¶

Submodules¶

models.resnet module¶

models.resnet.get_state_of_the_art_ILSVRC_resnet_model(model_name: str) → Tuple[torch.nn.modules.module.Module, int]¶

The get_state_of_the_art_ILSVRC_resnet_model() is designed based on PyTorch’s documentation to provide us with the state-of-the-art computer vision models for the task of image recognition.

model_name: str, required

The model name which is one of the list: [“resnet”, “alexnet”, “vgg”, “squeezenet”, “densenet”, “inception”]

This method returns a torch.nn.Module containing the model and the input size (one dimension of it only) for it.
